article.headline: Vermont 73, UMBC 58
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Marqus Blakely scored his third straight double-double with 17 points and 14 rebounds, and Vermont beat Maryland-Baltimore County 73-58 in the America East opener for both teams. Maurice Joseph added 16 points, Evan Fjeld had 13 and Garvey Young 11 for the Catamounts (10-5), who won their third game in a row and eighth out of their last nine. The Catamounts used an 11-2 run at the end of the first half to build a 39-28 halftime lead. UMBC cut the lead to 50-45 on a jumper by Shawn Grant with 10:14 remaining, but a few minutes later Vermont went on a 10-0 run to put the game out of reach at 65-49 with 5:17 to play. Blakely closed out the run with two free throws and a layup. It was the third straight loss for the Retrievers (1-12), who lost in the America East championship last season. Robbie Jackson led the Retrievers with 15 points and Gilliam Chauncey added 13.
